TRMS Overview\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 The purpose of TRMS is to provide a system that encourages quality knowledge growth relevant to an individual\rquote s expertise.   Currently, TRMS provides reimbursements for university courses, seminars, certification preparation classes, certifications, and technical training.  The decision has been made to develop a BPM solution for this system to improve the timeliness and accuracy of approvals.  The current system relies solely on email communication, requiring manual lookups of available funds and is error-prone due to inbox clutter and incorrect routing of tasks.  Furthermore, there is no way to record and report on reimbursements awarded, and so the company has no way to identify highly-invested courses that could be developed to be offered in-house.\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb40\sl240\slmult1\b\fs24 Business Rules\fs32\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 Each employee is allowed to claim \b up to $1000 \b0 in tuition \b reimbursement \b0 a year.  The amount available to an employee \b is reset on the new year\b0 . \par
Event types have different standard reimbursement coverage: \par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 University Courses 80%\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Seminars 60%\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Certification Preparation Classes 75%\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Certification 100%\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Technical Training 90%\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Other 30%\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1 After a BenCo has approved a reimbursement, the reimbursement is \b pending until a passing grade or presentation \b0 over the event is provided.\par
The monetary amount available for an employee to reimburse is defined by the following equation:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 AvailableReimburstment = TotalReimburstment ($1000) \f1\endash\f0  PendingReimburstments \f1\endash\f0  AwardedReimburstments.  \par

\pard\sl240\slmult1 If the projected reimbursement for an event exceeds the available reimbursement amount, it is adjusted to the amount available.  Reimbursements do not cover course materials such as books.\par

