\pard\keep\keepn\sb40\sl240\slmult1\b\fs24 Business Rules\fs32\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 Grading formats are pulled from a reference table.  Certain grading formats require the employee to perform a presentation to management after the event\rquote s completion and prior to awarded reimbursement.  A passing grade is needed for reimbursement otherwise.  Employee must provide the passing grade cutoff for the course, or choose to use a default passing grade if unknown.  If an employee provides an approval email, that approval step is skipped (cannot skip BenCo Approval).  If the course is < 2 weeks from beginning, the request is marked urgent.\par
A reimbursement request will have the following status types: \par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 NEW (Not Reviewed)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}NEEDS_MORE_INFO\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}ALTERED (BenCo altered the reimbursement amount and is waiting for employee approval.  The employee may cancel requests whose amount has been altered.)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}CANCELLED (Canceled by employee when reimbursement was adjusted by BenCo)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}CONFIRMED (Employee has confirmed the altered reimbursement amount)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}AWAITING_DECISION (Approved by BenCo, BenCo cannot deny a request)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}DENIED\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}DS_APPROVED (approved by direct supervisor)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}APPROVED (approved by department head)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}PENDING_PASSING (Approved but waiting for passing grade or presentation)\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}AWARDED\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb240\sl240\slmult1\b\fs40 Direct Supervisor Approval\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 The direct supervisor must provide approval for Tuition Reimbursement.  The Direct Supervisor can request additional information from the employee before approval. \par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb40\sl240\slmult1\b\fs24 Business Rules\fs32\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 If denied, the Direct Supervisor must provide a reason.  If the direct supervisor is also a department head, then the department head approval is skipped.  If the direct supervisor does not complete this task in a timely matter, the request is auto-approved. \par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb240\sl240\slmult1\b\fs40 Department Head Approval\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 The department head must provide approval for Tuition Reimbursement.  The Department Head can request additional information from the employee or direct supervisor before approval.\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb40\sl240\slmult1\b\fs24 Business Rules\fs32\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 If the Department Head does not complete this task in a timely matter, the request is auto-approved.  (Note, a department head has reports_to set to null)\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb240\sl240\slmult1\b\fs40 Benefits Coordinator Approval\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 The BenCo must provide approval for Tuition Reimbursement.   This stage is not skippable for any reason.  The BenCo can request additional information from the employee, direct supervisor, or department head before approval. The BenCo has the ability to alter the reimbursement amount.\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb40\sl240\slmult1\b\fs24 Business Rules\fs32\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 If the BenCo changes the reimbursement amount, the Employee should be notified and given the option to cancel the request.  If the BenCo does not approval in a timely matter, an escalation email should be sent to the BenCo\rquote s direct supervisor.  The BenCo is allowed to \b award \b0 an amount \b larger than the amount available \b0 (surpassing $1000 available) for the employee.  The BenCo must provide reason for this, and the reimbursement must be marked as exceeding available funds for reporting purposes.\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb240\sl240\slmult1\b\fs40 Grade/Presentation Upload\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 Upon completion of the event, the employee should attach either the Grade or Presentation as appropriate.  After upload of a grade, the BenCo must confirm that the grade is passing.  After upload of a presentation, the direct manager must confirm that the presentation was satisfactory and presented to the appropriate parties.  Upon confirmation, the amount is awarded to the requestor.\par

\pard\keep\keepn\sb40\sl240\slmult1\b\fs24 Business Rules\fs32\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b0\fs22 Only interested parties should be able to access the grades/presentations.  Interested parties include the requestor and approvers.  \par
